{"source_key":"sha256-852da461b9759bc2736926d9891eb9a3","record_index":5126,"record_hash":"sha256:0153fb163aa3679427464f2d40f59f40507d26287ecefd37a3bc2f2b88d4d4e4","timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:13:57.951Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 8071fd\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 829\nOutput:\n\n- `listSessions(project, filters, cursor)`\n- `getSessionTimeline(session_key, window?)`\n- `findRelatedSessions(target)`\n- `getRelatedSessionDetail(target, session_key, turn_window)`\n- `previewReviewShare(target)`\n\nProduct behavior:\n\n- Handoff reads a session timeline and can render records grouped by capture\n  turn or logical conversation/provider turn.\n- Review sharing starts from branch, review/PR, or change candidates, verifies\n  hits against `TurnDetail.observed_targets`, then scores related sessions at\n  read time.\n- Automatic association is private discovery. Anything exposed outside normal\n  repository-private scope must go through an explicit projection/redaction\n  step.\n- Results should be phrased as related-session evidence, not proof of authorship.\n\nV1 non-goals:\n\n- no durable inferred branch/PR/change ownership links\n- no path index\n- no commit index\n- no separate checked-out refs field\n- no graph `is_entrypoint` storage\n- no commit message summaries in capture turn snapshots\n- no index deletion/rebuild command\n\nThe rest of this document explains the rationale and implementation details\nbehind that contract.\n\n## Implementation Status\n\nAs of 2026-05-20, the `crates/but-agentlog` POC has moved from storage design\ninto the read/use-case layer.\n\nImplemented:\n\n- capture turns are persisted only when capture accepts new transcript records\n- transcript dedupe returns ordered accepted records for the capture invocation\n- `TurnSummary` and `TurnDetail` are stored in GitMeta\n- `TurnDetail.records` is ordered and authoritative for turn rendering\n- `turn_key` uses the specified truncated SHA-256 identity over session,\n  source, and ordered record hashes\n- transcript record hashes use the `sha256:<full lowercase hex digest>` shape\n- `previous_turn_key` links to the previous committed turn in the same session\n- session/source metadata, transcript records, record hashes, turn summary,\n  turn detail, and index memberships are written in one GitMeta `apply_edits`\n  batch\n- capture has a repo-local lock around the read/dedupe/write section\n- environment snapshots are captured best-effort and can be enriched later when\n  capture observes no new transcript records\n- branch, review, and change indexes are written from `observed_targets`\n- read helpers exist for session listing, session timelines, related-session\n  lookup, related-session scoring, and related-session detail hydration\n\nStill left for the v1 internal POC:\n\n- add the `previewReviewShare(target)` read facade\n- decide the small preview payload shape: target, related sessions, scores,\n  highlighted turns, redacted records, and enough evidence for UI copy\n- keep the preview read-only; it should not persist ownership, links, or share\n  state\n- wire the read helpers into the intended API/product boundary when the payload\n  shape is stable\n- choose the handoff surface: likely session list plus timeline windowing\n- add product-level tests around preview/handoff payloads once the API boundary\n  exists\n\nGitMeta owns the metadata persistence and distribution mechanism. `but-agentlog`\nowns the agentlog-specific projection: selecting related sessions/turns,\nredacting transcript payloads, and showing the user exactly what would be shared\nbefore anything leaves normal repository-private scope.\n\n## Product Use Cases\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T15:13:57.951Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}